exception use cases.

00:02:49.790 --> 00:02:52.910
So for example, if one of my
goods suddenly started getting

00:02:52.910 --> 00:02:55.920
a high charge-back rate, this is
where I would go to try to

00:02:55.920 --> 00:02:59.980
diagnose the issue, understand
if a particular country was

00:02:59.980 --> 00:03:01.680
causing the problem or
whether I was seeing

00:03:01.680 --> 00:03:04.060
this across all countries.

00:03:04.060 --> 00:03:06.790
